ally if there's some guidance. Since it looks like no extra setup is needed, I’ll go with no action, but I'd note the API migration risks.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra dependency, Docker image, environment variable, or system property is concretely required. The 4.0.0 pooled artifact depends only on neo4j-bolt-connection at compile/runtime, and meaningful coverage can be reached with in-test fakes for BoltConnectionProvider, AuthTokenManager, SecurityPlanSupplier, MetricsListener, and LoggingProvider.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The javac failure is primarily an API migration issue: 4.0.0 replaces/removes several 3.0.0-era types such as PooledBoltConnectionProvider, RoutingContext, and DatabaseNameUtil. Tests must target PooledBoltConnectionSource and the 4.0.0 BoltConnectionProvider signature.\",\n    \"A real Neo4j server or the netty provider may be useful for integration-style tests, but upstream pooled tests exercise the pooling behavior with mocked or fake providers, so Docker setup is not required for meaningful generated coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0b562c7a9ac65006016a3ed61e88688196bfa4203976884157\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2289, "output": 644, "cacheRead": 30208, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33141, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782502934350, "responseId": "resp_0b562c7a9ac65006016a3ed616ec34819682d1f3f8fce5575d"}, "toolResults": []}
